Name: Cogs
Description: Common material that contains important compounds.
WorldDesc: Standard cog widely used in industrial production during the Golden Age. It became the key to Construct development when the Ta-193 copolymer that it contains was found to have extremely high biological affinity.

Description: Special card that can be exchanged for various materials.
WorldDesc: Can be exchanged for resources in Humanity Front territory. Issued to squads as funding and managed by the Commandant.

Name: Serum
Description: Required for the Commandant to enter battle.
WorldDesc: Protects the human body from the Punishing for a certain amount of time, and supplied to Babylonia's frontline squads reguarly.

Name: Friendship Point
Description: Level of friendship with a contact.

Description: Data program that increases members' understanding of skills and raises their skill levels.

Description: Activity gained from completing Daily Missions. Resets at 07:00 AM UTC daily.

Name: Weekly Activity
Description: Activity gained from completing Daily Missions. Resets at 07:00 AM UTC on Monday.

Name: Particle
Description: Generated by the Dormitory power plant.

Name: Material
WorldDesc: Materials obtained from recycling. Can be remade into various useful items.

WorldDesc: Robot developed by Babylonia. Able to survive exposure to the Punishing for brief periods of time, it can help find useful materials on the battlefield.

Name: Bounty EXP
WorldDesc: Special reward that increases Bounty level. Complete different missions to get different bonuses. "Aim for the top." —Anonymous Construct

Name: Test item
WorldDesc: Test item

Name: Current
Description: Progress earned from completing Novice Missions.
WorldDesc: Thank you, Commandant. - Gray Raven

Name: Fragment Shard
WorldDesc: Different combinations of the same shards may lead to different results. - Asimov

Name: Scavenger MK-II
WorldDesc: Robot developed by Babylonia. Able to survive exposure to the Punishing for brief periods of time, it can help find useful materials on the battlefield.

Name: War Zone Influence
Description: Currency for War Zone. Can be used in the War Shop.
WorldDesc: Conflicts of various kinds can arise in the War Zone. Those who have influence are often in a position to determine the final outcome of these Event.

Name: 4★ Weapon Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 4★ weapon. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 5★ Weapon Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 5★ weapon. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 6★ Weapon Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 6★ weapon. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 4★ Memory Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 4★ Memory Chip. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 5★ Memory Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 5★ Memory Chip. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 6★ Memory Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 6★ Memory Chip. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: Dorm Coin
Description: Used for Dormitory Research and other actions.
WorldDesc: Shiny coins that can be spent to perform research and other Dormitory-related actions.

Name: Decor Coin
Description: Parts obtained from recycling Decor. Can be reassembled into other Decor.
WorldDesc: Recycle existing Decor to obtain materials to produce new Decor, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: Coating Blueprint
WorldDesc: Design blueprint that records Coating schematics in detail, used to produce new Coatings.

Name: Coating Sketch
Description: Can be exchanged for Coating Blueprints.
WorldDesc: Rough sketch of a Coating design. Conveys the designer's concept, but not quite detailed enough to put into production.

Name: A-Class Inver Material
WorldDesc: Material obtained from recycling Inver-Shards. Highly valuable and can be exchanged for various supplies at Babylonia.

Name: S-Class Inver Material
WorldDesc: Material obtained from recycling Inver-Shards. Extremely valuable and can be exchanged for various supplies at Babylonia.

Name: Residence Permit
Description: Used to unlock a new Dormitory.
WorldDesc: Permit to build new Dormitory facilities at the HQ.

Name: Proof of Honor
Description: Upvote others members of the United Command Bureau to increase their Popularity.
WorldDesc: A special proof of popularity.

Name: Command Bureau Contribution
Description: Indicates the contribution you have made to the Command Bureau. Forms the basis for Command Bureau Contribution Rankings.
WorldDesc: Can be gained by participating in Command Bureau challenges

Name: United Achievement Points
Description: Rewarded to participants in Command Bureau challenges. Can be exchanged for various resources in Point Shop.
WorldDesc: Tokens rewarded to participants in Command Bureau events

Name: Command Bureau EXP
Description: You can level up the Command Bureau after gaining enough Command Bureau EXP.
WorldDesc: You can accumulate EXP for your Command Bureau by participating in Command Bureau challenges.

Name: Return Progress
Description: The progress of returning player missions. Will be reset once the returning period ends.

Name: Type II Vote
Description: Use this item to give likes to your favorite comments in Eden II forum.
WorldDesc: Each vote has a unique identification code. Enter the code in Eden II to get likes. The votes will be reset to zero at the end of every event.

Name: Progress
Description: The progress of completion for Eden II Event targets.
WorldDesc: Thank you, Commandant. - Gray Raven

Name: Pioneer Medal
Description: The proof of participation in the pioneer test. Can be exchanged for Black Cards in the live server. Stay tuned to further announcements for more detail.

Name: Weapon Coating Blueprint
Description: Can be exchanged for Weapon Coatings.
WorldDesc: Design blueprint that records Weapon Coating schematics in detail, used to produce new Weapon Coatings.

Name: Beacon Amplifier Points
Description: Gained by leveling up the Command Bureau. Allow you to level up Beacon Amplifier.
WorldDesc: An indicator of the team effort put into developing the Command Bureau.

Name: Special Support Token
Description: Can be exchanged for items in Resource Shop.
WorldDesc: A silver spinning top crafted from special materials. Bears a QR code that projects the words "Support Force" upon being scanned. Can be exchanged in Resource Shop for supplies that Babylonia has specially requisitioned for high-performing squads.

Name: S-Rank Transcendant Material
WorldDesc: Material obtained from recycling Transcendant Shards. Highly valuable and can be exchanged for various supplies in Babylonia.

Name: Action Points
WorldDesc: Autopoiesis Maze Action Points

Name: Aberrant Cube
Description: Can purchase add-on units in Autopoiesis Maze
WorldDesc: The smaller version of a common material for industrial production. Can quickly produce add-ons and tools, among other things, based on the blueprint provided. Caveat: non-standard materials like this are worthless outside Autopoiesis Maze.

Name: Add-On Unit
Description: Gain a random add-on unit to power up members in Autopoiesis Maze.
WorldDesc: An integrator of certain add-on efficacy. Only works in Autopoiesis Maze.

Name: Strange Mark
WorldDesc: Its nature is completely unknown.

Name: Popular Gift
Description: Can be gifted to another Commandant in the Command Bureau. The recipient gains 10 Popularity while the giver receives 1 United Achievement Point.
WorldDesc: Can be gained by playing the combat supply stage AE-5

Name: Phantom Pain Scar
Description: Obtained from Phantom Pain Cage. Can be exchanged for useful items
WorldDesc: Parts retrieved from powerful Corrupted, key to unlocking the secrets of the Punishing Virus. Can be exchanged for supplies.

Name: HQ Shard
Description: Made from scrap metal. Can be exchanged for items with the Support Force.

Name: Shark-speare Figurine
Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Park Parade."
WorldDesc: A 1:15 limited-edition Shark-speare figurine gained after "playing" with Shark-speare, with quality varying depending on the level. All it ever does is play the same nursery rhyme over and over: "Let's play and be friends! Shark-speare loves eating the Gingerbread Man!"

Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Park Parade." (Collectible upgraded to blue)

Name: Challenge Medal
Description: Hard quests have a chance to drop these tokens, which can be exchanged for materials.

Name: Tokarev Tower Badge
Description: Project Babel—A badge obtained from Tokarev. It is a valuable collection that can be of great use in the future.
WorldDesc: Used to reward the commandants who succeeded in an in-depth simulation of Project Babel tactical operation. The number of badges offered depends on the tactical level reached. it is delicately crafted with special sentimental value.

Name: Sand Tower Badge
Description: Project Babel—A badge obtained from the desert. The exquisite craftsmanship enhances its value to collectors.
WorldDesc: Used to reward the commandants who succeeded in an in-depth simulation of the 2nd Project Babel tactical operation, Sands of Infinity. The number of badges offered depends on the tactical level reached. As proof of glory and valiance, it is exquisitely crafted with special collection value.

Name: Theme Park Tower Badge
Description: A badge obtained from Project Babel—Theme Park. Makes a valuable collectible.
WorldDesc: Rewarded to Commandants who have succeeded in an in-depth simulation of Project Babel tactical operation phase 3. Hand-crafted and exquisitely designed to commemorate an unforgettable experience. (Badge upgraded to blue)

Name: Theme Park Tower Badge
Description: A badge obtained from Project Babel—Theme Park. Makes a valuable collectible.
WorldDesc: Rewarded to Commandants who have succeeded in an in-depth simulation of Project Babel tactical operation phase 3. Hand-crafted and exquisitely designed to commemorate an unforgettable experience. (Badge upgraded to purple)

Name: Theme Park Tower Badge
Description: A badge obtained from Project Babel—Theme Park. Makes a valuable collectible.
WorldDesc: Rewarded to Commandants who have succeeded in an in-depth simulation of Project Babel tactical operation phase 3. Hand-crafted and exquisitely designed to commemorate an unforgettable experience. (Badge upgraded to orange)

Name: Nightmare Medal
Description: Mark of recognition for completing the main quest on Nightmare difficulty.
WorldDesc: Granted only to those who have overcome the most difficult of challenges.

Name: Portable Game Console
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Kamui's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: The newest portable game console, perfect for passing the time between missions. Who is behind the anonymous account at the top of the rankings?

Name: MRE Rations
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Watanabe's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Popular ration set that contains a main dish, a side course, and coffee. You may even get rare seasoning such as miso if you are lucky.

Name: Liliy Brooch
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Bianca's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: The lily represents selflessness and dignity.

Name: Painting Kit
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Ayla's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A painting kit released by the most popular art supply brand "Montpellier", which is dedicated to sharing the happiness of artistic creation to everyone. Montpellier is always an artist's choice.

Name: High-Power Batteries
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Sophia's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Batteries for power tools. No mechanics want to find themselves out of batteries during work, right?

Name: R3 Cleaning Robot
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Chrome's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Developed by Cosmos Industries for Babylonia's domestic market, this cleaning robot is the best solution to a nice and clean environment.

Name: Military-Grade Bionic Dog
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Vera's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A small military-grade bionic dog that performs various functions from item storage to radar detection, with its absolute loyalty to its master being its biggest selling point. It's been widely acclaimed ever since it was released by General Toys.

Name: Media Player
Description: Increases Transcendant Affection. Camu's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A peripheral media player device attached to a Construct. Can receive messages and signals from Babylonia.

Name: Best-Seller
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Common gift that everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Serialized manga that has been a best-seller both on a ground and in Babylonia since the last century, depicting the human struggle against the Punishing Virus.

Name: Vinyl Record
Description: Increases members' Affection. A common gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Specialized teams have been sent to earth to retrieve the sounds, sights and culture that could not be artificially recreated, resulting in this record of a golden era long gone.

Name: Ration Chocolate
Description: Increases members' Affection. An exquisite gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Chocolate bar used as rations by the United Earth military. Has a very long shelf life with a wide variety of flavors. A delicious gift.

Name: 1 Day Tour Tickets x2
Description: Increases Construct Affection. Fine gift that everybody likes.
WorldDesc: A pair of bracelet tickets for 2 people to enjoy a day tour of Babylonia, including transport, space observation deck tickets, VIP hologram theater seats, as well as bar and outdoor pool party access.

Name: Normal Gift Box
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Fine Gift Box
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Precious Gift Box
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Sweet Gift Box
Description: Choose 1 from 3 gifts: Precision Toolkit, Portable Game Console, MRE Rations.
WorldDesc: A gift box wrapped with a ribbon. It contains male Construct's favorite gifts.

Name: Beating Heart Gift
Description: Choose 1 from 6 gifts: Frog Accessory, Biosphere, Jack-in-the-box, Prototype Engine, Liliy Brooch, Painting Kit.
WorldDesc: An exquisite gift box that contains female Construct's favorite gifts.

Name: Crimson Love
Description: Constructs give this rare collectible to their Commandant on May 20th. It carries special meanings.
WorldDesc: Constructs have prepared this rose for a special day. It's been carefully sealed within a box so it can be preserved permanently.

Name: White Affection
Description: All Constructs love this rare gift. Give it to them on a special day to create some great memories.
WorldDesc: A customized rose for your important ones. Costs a lot to make, and contains a lot of emotions.

Name: Serum Bundle (XL) [abandoned]
WorldDesc: Extra large Serum bundle for the Commandant's use. Holds a huge amount of Serum.

Name: Serum Bundle (XXL) [abandoned]
WorldDesc: Double extra large Serum bundle for the Commandant's use. Holds a massive amount of Serum.

Name: Reagent He-4
Description: Fusion reagent dropped from deep ocean Corrupted. Can be exchanged for items in Frozen Darkness.
WorldDesc: Deep ocean Corrupted store He-4 generated by their internal fusion reactors in special containers, which are considered valuable resources.

Name: Overclock Material Box (α)
Description: Gives a random low-grade overclock material.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Overclock Material Box (β)
Description: Gives a random high-grade overclock material.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Christmas Decor Blueprint Set
WorldDesc: A fine Christmas gift box. No way to know which blueprint is inside without opening it.

Name: Heteromer Sample
Description: A sample of Hetero-matter produced by Hetero-Core that can be used in exchange for supplies in Aerial Supply.
WorldDesc: Hetero-derivatives are produced by the Punishing Virus under special environmental conditions. Dense and solid in texture, its behaviors are far more complicated than that of Punishing Virus.

Name: Space Station Battlelog
Description: A battlelog from the space station that can be used in exchange for Battlelog Reward.
WorldDesc: This battlelog not only records and summarizes the combats that occurred every day but also helps you figure out how to enrich Construct's combat experience and skills... Someone said and took out a precious Space Station Battlelog Collector's Edition.

Name: Heteromer Crystal
Description: Raw material for Heteromer Layer Experiment. Conduct Heteromer Layer Experiment to get the Research supplies from Babylonia.
WorldDesc: The pure nucleus formed because of the large structure fluctuation of liquid Hetero-matter. The top-tier scientists of Babylonia are dedicated to the study of Hetero-Core through Heteromer Crystal.

Name: Akdilek Coin
Description: Currency issued by Akdilek that can be used in exchange for items in the event shop.
WorldDesc: With a high level of trading proficiency, Akdilek Commercial Alliance has turned Akdilek Coin into a currency that is even more valuable than rare metals in various regions. Now it is one of the most popular currencies for trading.

Name: Magnetic Ticket
Description: Eternal Throne Abyss Pass (returns 6★ Memory Shard x10 when expired)
WorldDesc: A brand new first-class magnetic ticket with an Akdilek logo and station number. It can be used to enter certain special regions.

Name: Royal Token
Description: A royal token from Asslam that is given as a reward for outstanding merit. Can be used in exchange for corresponding rewards.
WorldDesc: If one can earn respect and trust from the aristocrats on the train, this rare token will be offered as the highest honor given by them.

Name: Support Point
Description: Support permit issued by Babylonia. Can be used to apply for different supports from Babylonia during the mission.
WorldDesc: To support commandants' operation, Babylonia provides support points that can be used to request different supports from Babylonia without President's authorization.

Name: Metal Grub
Description: A currency circulating around the Nighter. Can be used in the Virtual Mart.
WorldDesc: Even when separated, the offspring of the mythological water-beetle qingfu will always return to their mother. Issued by the KCC, the qingfu coin is a symbol of accumulating wealth. Also called grub by the locals.

Name: Holographic Ticket
Description: Cornered in Cruise - Abyss Pass (returns 6★ Memory Shard x10 when expired)
WorldDesc: The first class ticket issued by Kowloong Chamber of Commerce. Use it to watch a holographic puppet show of the performance troupe up close.

Name: Electronic Stamp
Description: Issued by the financial department of KCC, this Electronic Stamp has "Qu" printed on it and can be exchanged for items via the terminals.
WorldDesc: The Electronic Stamps backed by the leader of KCC, "Qu", are proofs of transactions on the Nighter. It serves as both an ID and a trade credit across all the financial terminals.

Name: Titanium Token
Description: Forged from titanium extracted from scrapped mechanical parts, this token is chosen as a widely circulating currency in the microchip market for its lightness and corrosion resistance.
WorldDesc: A new alloy currency issued under the authorization of Asimov, this token is only available in the Memory Chip market. It also works as an ID and a certificate of the Memory Chip knowledge, and is necessary for the purchase of any high-spec components.

Name: Crystal Note
Description: A currency circulating in Kowloong Metropolis. Can be exchanged for items in Kowloong Market.
WorldDesc: An easy-to-carry, ultra slim transaction card issued by Bank of Kowloong. Made from semi-transparent micro crystals, this card has a micro-photon chip inside. A complicated circuit-like glowing pattern is printed on its surface. —"Bank of Kowloong specializes in everything."

Name: Dragon Jade
Description: Dragon Jades are only produced in Kowlong City. They can be exchanged for items in Rosary Path.
WorldDesc: A glossy jade pendant with a vivid floating dragon carved on it. Rumor has it that some mysterious merchants would offer a fortune for this luxurious token...

Name: Morning Star Cup
Description: Randomly dropped in event stages that have a Serum cost. Can be exchanged for Sorbet Summer event mission rewards.
WorldDesc: The Venus Splash Park limited edition ice-cream cup. Ticket holders can get a free cup from A'Mao. Made from strawberries, chocolate flakes, cream, and a paper card of Shark-speare. Note: The paper is not edible.

Name: Square Chip
Description: Can be used to flip one tile in Summer Flip.
WorldDesc: An exquisite square chip, used as a token for the wildly popular board game in the central arcade in Venus Splash Park. Win a certain amount of them and you get to take home all the prizes sealed away in the glass cabinet. Want to try your luck?

Name: One-Point Dice
Description: Can be used in Summer Flip. Allows you to select a reward icon and move it one tile.
WorldDesc: A beautifully crafted six-sided dice, used in the board game in the central arcade of Venus Splash Park. All its six sides bear the same number: "1"—so no matter how you throw it, you will always wind up moving one step.

Name: Summer Photo Puzzle Piece 1
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Photo.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Photo.

Name: Summer Photo Puzzle Piece 2
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Photo.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Photo.

Name: Summer Photo Puzzle Piece 3
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Photo.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Photo.

Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Photo.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Photo.

Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Photo.

WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Photo.

Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Photo.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Photo.

Name: Summer Photo Puzzle Piece 8
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Photo.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Photo.

Name: Hypertune Material Pack
Description: Gives Hypertune Crystal α x300, Hypertune Crystal β x50, Hypertune Catalyst α x9, and Hypertune Catalyst β x3
WorldDesc: Contains the materials needed to complete a Hypertune

Name: Hypertune Crystal α
Description: Use it to purchase Hypertune Crystals from the Hypertune Shop.
WorldDesc: Extracted and reforged from Hypertune Crystals, this crystal coin is a commonly used token in the Hypertune Shop.

Name: Hypertune Crystal β
Description: Use it to purchase Extreme (β) Hypertune Crystals from the Hypertune Shop.
WorldDesc: Extracted and reforged from Extreme (β) Hypertune Crystals, this crystal coin is a commonly used token in the Hypertune Shop.

Name: Condelina Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: The Torch of Thinking — Where the original copy of this great work was found is still unknown, but age has taken its toll on the book and it is now hardly interpretable. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Condelina Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Pure Reason — A lengthy, sophisticated masterpiece of philosophy that laid the foundation of many great theories in the old world. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Shakespeare Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Incomplete Scripts — Fragments of an old-world theater play, with some touching stories written on them. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Shakespeare Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Summer Night's Dream — A story about an interesting incident caused by naughty fairies on a summer night. Seems to be highly popular in the old world. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Heisen Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Replica Circuit — A mass-produced replica circuit that took reference from the human brain. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Heisen Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Precision Circuit — A highly sophisticated, precision-machined electronic circuit. Even great scholars would take a lengthy time to study and understand its structure. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Darwin Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: The Outline of Evolution — An outline that resembles a mind map of early-age studies on the origin of creatures. Albeit very brief, it still clearly demonstrates the intelligence of its author. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Darwin Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Abstracts of the Origin of Species — A scientific theory that brought revolution to biology and is still used as an evidence of evolution until today. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Hanna Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Crude Piano Model — A crude model of a mini-piano made out of concepts that still requires a significant amount of work. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality

Name: Hanna Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Wood Piano Model — Crafted from pure timber, this mini-piano model looks so real that one can almost press its keys to play a song. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Cottie Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Doughnut (Low Sugar) — An ordinary-looking low sugar dessert. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Cottie Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Doughnut Box — A gift box consisting of doughnuts made by pastry chefs all around the globe. The doughnuts inside look great and taste delicious without being too sweet. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Da Vinci Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Sketch of Machines — A passionate machine enthusiast's sketch of some mechanical concepts, ranging from basic robots to powered vehicles. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Da Vinci Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Da Vinci's Cryptex — An encrypted tube consisting of 5 rotating alphabetic discs. Rumor has it that secrets are stored inside the tube, but breaking it by force will destroy its content forever. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Catherine Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Flower Bud — This bud was made into a dry specimen before it bloomed so it could be preserved longer. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Catherine Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Red Blossom — A new sample of fresh red rose. Its rotating petals and juicy red color are still highly sought after by many collectors. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Einsteina Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Unfinished Works — An excerpt paying tribute to the original author's academic philosophy, but incomplete for some unknown reason. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Einsteina Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Theory of Relativity (Abstract) — A theory that revolutionized physics and is still seen as the pinnacle of wisdom today. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Philip II Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Silver Alloy Flute — A beautifully crafted flute that is also corrosion resistant, making it a decent option for flute enthusiasts. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Philip II Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Pure Platinum Flute — Its delicate looks suggest an expensive price tag for this hand-crafted instrument. The pure, bright timbre gives the listeners a refreshing feel. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Guinevere Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Glamorous Shard — This timeworn shard used to be part of some luxurious ornament and had witnessed a great but pitiful time. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Guinevere Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Laurel Crown — A corona weaved from laurel leaves for the beauty. It gives a nice fragrance. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Frederick Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Unnamed Music Sheet — No one knows what this simple and pleasant music is called, or where it comes from. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Frederick Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Flute Concerto — This renowned concerto is elegant, passionate and bold, yet has great attention to detail. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Bathlon Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Rusty Badge — This timeworn badge no longer shines, but the honor it carries has not faded a bit. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Bathlon Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Gem Scepter — Crafted from precious metals, this scepter is decorated with many gems, and has a flying eagle carved on the disc at the top. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Patton Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Silver Medal — Forged from silver alloys, this medal is often awarded to those who have made outstanding contribution in one or more areas. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Patton Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Royal Medal — On this medal are lions, unicorns, and a shield in the center. Only those who are kind, brave, and have made great contribution can receive this honor. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Zu Wenyuan Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Measuring Tools — Various types of advanced measuring tools that are easy to carry and manufacture, yet have great precision. Form part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Zu Wenyuan Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Mathematics Collection — A collection of many mathematics models and their solutions that represents the development of mathematics over time, and still has great significance in precision calculation and measuring. Forms part of the Memory Chip's signal frequency and can be used to improve the chip quality.

Name: Koya Hypertune α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Life Support Set: A toolbox once used by Koya. Contains various tools that can be used for combat support, defense fortification, and emergency rescue. Accounts for a section of the chip's signal spectrum and can be used to upgrade the chip.

Name: Koya Hypertune β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Mottled Photo: A photo of two young boys, one blue-haired and one blond. Their faces, bathed in the sunset glow, are barely invisible. This item accounts for a section of the chip's signal spectrum and can be used to upgrade the chip.

Name: Hypertune Catalyst α
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Generates a highly volatile catalytic reaction in the Memory Chip's internal compounds which leads to the forming of low-level bonds between micro particles. Part of the new Memory signals are formed during the reaction.

Name: Hypertune Catalyst β
Description: Used as a material in Memory Hypertune.
WorldDesc: Generates an extremely volatile catalytic reaction in the Memory Chip's internal compounds which leads to the forming of high-level bonds between micro particles. New Memory signals are rapidly formed during the reaction.

Name: Benizakura
WorldDesc: A katana used by the Performer Puppets to perform an ethereal blade dance.

Name: Iris
WorldDesc: Beautiful things come with thorns, the same as this bow does.

Name: Firecrackers
WorldDesc: Its design is inspired by firecrackers. The firecrackers on the tail can be loaded into the barrel as a projectile. It has a several second downtime after every shot.

Name: Hymn of Stars
WorldDesc: A Christmas elf is said to come with cheery tintinnabulations in snow, and at this time, snowflakes fly as if they are celebrating her arrival—Shh... You heard that? Here she is!

Name: Coating Pick Supply Pack
WorldDesc: Choose 1 from 14 Coatings: Gray Feathers: Palefire, Gray Feathers: Storm, Gray Feathers: Blast, Gray Feathers: Ember, Gray Feathers: Lotus, Gray Feathers: Eclipse, Gray Feathers: Pulse, Gray Feathers: Lux, Gray Feathers: Dawn, Demon Gear, Thistle, Gothic Sentinel, Ashen End, Shooting Star.

Name: B-Rank Construct Pick
Description: Choose one from 3 B-Rank Constructs: Lotus, Storm, Eclipse.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: A-Rank Construct Pick
Description: Choose one from 6 A-Rank Constructs: Dawn, Lux, Palefire, Zero, Blast, Nightblade.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: New Year Gift
WorldDesc: The gift obtained from New Year event. Give it to Constructs.

Name: Gray Feathers: Palefire
WorldDesc: The customized uniform made for all the Constructs that have developed a bond with Gray Raven. Often worn as a formal dress during all important events.

WorldDesc: The customized uniform made for all the Constructs that have developed a bond with Gray Raven. Often worn as a formal dress during all important events.

WorldDesc: The special ports on this outfit keep Karenina in sync with her action-support system, so she can adapt to fast-accelerating, intensive combat situations.

WorldDesc: The customized uniform made for all the Constructs that have developed a bond with Gray Raven. Often worn as a formal dress during all important events.

WorldDesc: The customized uniform made for all the Constructs that have developed a bond with Gray Raven. Often worn as a formal dress during all important events.

Name: Thistle
WorldDesc: This elegant outfit borrows elements from the special crystal structure of refined ores found in regions of deep corrosion.

Name: Gothic
WorldDesc: Cruel yet elegant, she is one of the most formidable candidates in the ring. Still, many dream to become her new owner and take her away.

Name: Ashen End
WorldDesc: Equipped with built-in virus filter at the neck, enhanced alloy arms and converging leg armor, as well as independent bionic eyes. No prey could ever run away from the wearer of this outfit.

Name: Gray Feathers: Lotus
WorldDesc: The customized uniform made for all the Constructs that have developed a bond with Gray Raven. Often worn as a formal dress during all important events.

Name: Gray Feathers: La Paix
WorldDesc: The customized uniform made for all the Constructs that have developed a bond with Gray Raven. Often worn as a formal dress during all important events.

Name: Shooting Star
WorldDesc: Each time this unit is deployed, soldiers could see a shooting star falling into the battlefield. The brilliant light is a result of burning armor under high-powered propulsion.

Name: Maid of Time
WorldDesc: 7:00, good morning. 9:00, saying goodbye. 11:00, a morning tea alone. 1:00, ironing clothes. 3:00, cleaning the room. 5:00, preparing for dinner. 6:00, eagerly awaiting. 8:00, welcome back.

Name: Volatile Priestess
WorldDesc: This coating was recreated based on ancient legends from the database, where gods were calmed and worshipped by humans. Perhaps the wearer of this outfit would also make a suited choice in the post-apocalyptic world corrupted by Punishing.

Name: Spring Breeze
WorldDesc: Orioles hop around bamboos as the spring breeze gently goes past trees, bringing fallen petals back to the branches.

Name: Arctic A-Rank Construct Pick
Description: Choose one from 12 A-Rank Constructs: Dawn, Lux, Palefire, Zero, Blast, Nightblade, Bastion, Astral, Brilliance, Silverfang, Arclight, and Rozen.
WorldDesc: Use it in Items > Item.

Name: Gray Feathers: Crimson Abyss
WorldDesc: The customized uniform made for all the Constructs that have developed a bond with Gray Raven. Often worn as a formal dress during all important Event.

Name: Gray Feathers: Bastion
WorldDesc: The customized uniform made for all the Constructs that have developed a bond with Gray Raven. Often worn as a formal dress during all important Event.

Name: End Messenger
WorldDesc: The enhanced lower-body structure allows the wearer of this outfit to quickly dashes across cities full of obstacles. Also has a low-level virus filter installed.

Name: ホワイトデーの騎士
Description: 異火、重力、夜刃、景星のうち、好きな1体を獲得できる。
